## rigour
Definition 7.1 in the lecture notes.

direct_product:= Let $G_1$ and $G_2$ be two groups. Then $G=G_1\times G_2 = \left\{  (g_1,g_2) : g_1 \in G_1, g_2 \in G_2\right\}$ with the multiplication law $(g_1,g_2)(g_1', g_2') = \left( g_1g_1',g_2g_2' \right)$. $G_1\times G_2$ is called the direct_product of $G_1$ and $G_2$. The action is sort of [[dot_product]].
